 must enable it in test code via Typesafe Config, because pekko.actor.allow-java-serialization defaults to off; this is optional feature-specific configuration, not required setup for baseline actor coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0538949f5c9ecc49016a42a253c48881949ac2972f1500c7ce\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1735, "output": 842, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27665, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782751817262, "responseId": "resp_0538949f5c9ecc49016a42a249be5481948b94c3c4a81ef6a0"}}
